text: Acleris expressa is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in South Korea, China, Russia (Amur) and Japan. The wingspan is 19–22 mm. The larvae feed on Fraxinus mandshurica.Check List of the Tribe Tortricini (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) in Northeast china, with Two Newly Recorded Species from China ==References== Category:Moths described in 1931 expressa Category:Moths of Asia
